<mediaPoint id="fig01_6" type="IMG" mediaType="TID1" mediaSize="3" order="8" href="chap01.html#fig01_6"><desc><![CDATA[<b>Figure 1-6</b> Contributions to the ciliary ganglion. <span style="font-size:0.8em"><i>(Reproduced with permission from Doxanas MT, Anderson RL.</i> Clinical Orbital Anatomy. <i>Baltimore: Williams &#x0026; Wilkins; 1984.)</i></span>]]></desc><mediaPath src="images/img_p12-1.jpg" thumbSrc="images/img_p12-1.jpg"/></mediaPoint>
<mediaPoint id="fig01_7" type="IMG" mediaType="TID1" mediaSize="3" order="9" href="chap01.html#fig01_7"><desc><![CDATA[<b>Figure 1-7</b> Cranial nerve III and ciliary ganglion. The sympathetic fibers from the carotid artery are not shown (see Fig 1-6). <span style="font-size:0.8em"><i>(Illustration by Sylvia Barker.)</i></span>]]></desc><mediaPath src="images/img_p12-2.jpg" thumbSrc="images/img_p12-2.jpg"/></mediaPoint>
