</mediaMap>
<navPoint id="navPoint-19" playOrder="28"><navLabel><text>Extraocular Muscle Insertions</text></navLabel><content src="chap01.html#s17"/>
<mediaMap>
<mediaPoint id="fig01_12" type="IMG" mediaType="TID1" mediaSize="3" order="14" href="chap01.html#fig01_12"><desc><![CDATA[<b>Figure 1-12</b> The medial rectus tendon is closest to the limbus, and the superior rectus tendon is farthest from it. By connecting the insertions of the tendons beginning with the medial rectus, then the inferior rectus, then the lateral rectus, and finally the superior rectus, a spiral (known as the <i>spiral of Tillaux)</i> is obtained. Measurements are in millimeters. <span style="font-size:0.8em"><i>(Illustration by Christine Gralapp.)</i></span>]]></desc><mediaPath src="images/img_p14-3.jpg" thumbSrc="images/img_p14-3.jpg"/></mediaPoint>
<mediaPoint id="chap01_tab1" type="TAB" mediaType="TID4" mediaSize="3" order="15" href="chap01.html#chap01_tab1"><desc><![CDATA[]]></desc><mediaPath src="table01-1.xhtml" thumbSrc="images/img_p15-1.jpg"/></mediaPoint>
