<mediaPoint id="fig03_10" type="IMG" mediaType="TID1" mediaSize="3" order="94" href="chap03.html#fig03_10"><desc><![CDATA[<b>Figure 3-10</b> Cranial nerve V complex (dorsal view of brainstem). M = motor nucleus; MES = mesencephalic nucleus; MSN = main sensory nucleus; SN = spinal nucleus and tract; TG = trigeminal ganglion. A, B, and C represent portions of the caudal spinal nucleus that correspond to concentric areas of the face.]]></desc><mediaPath src="images/img_p98.jpg" thumbSrc="images/img_p98.jpg"/></mediaPoint>
</mediaMap>
