<mediaMap>
<mediaPoint id="fig03_16" type="IMG" mediaType="TID1" mediaSize="3" order="100" href="chap03.html#fig03_16"><desc><![CDATA[<b>Figure 3-16</b> <b>A,</b> Magnetic resonance angiogram showing the circle of Willis in an anteroposterior view. <b>B,</b> An oblique view from the same patient. ACA = anterior cerebral artery; BA = basilar artery; MCA = middle cerebral artery; PCA = posterior cerebral artery; PCoA = posterior communicating artery. <span style="font-size:0.8em"><i>(Courtesy of T. Talli, MD, and W. Yuh, MD.)</i></span>]]></desc><mediaPath src="images/img_p107ab.jpg" thumbSrc="images/img_p107ab.jpg"/></mediaPoint>
