<mediaMap>
<mediaPoint id="fig07_2" type="IMG" mediaType="TID1" mediaSize="3" order="145" href="chap07.html#fig07_2"><desc><![CDATA[<b>Figure 7-2</b> Schematic drawing of the major tear glands and ocular surface epithelia that contribute to the tear film. Shown are the meibomian glands (secrete oily layer); accessory lacrimal glands and lacrimal glands of Henle and Manz (secrete aqueous layer); conjunctival epithelium; corneal epithelium; and conjunctival goblet cells (secrete mucus layer). <span style="font-size:0.8em"><i>(From Dartt DA, Sullivan DA. Wetting of the ocular surface. In: Albert DM, Jakobiec FA, eds.</i> Principles and Practice of Ophthalmology. <i>Philadelphia: Saunders; 1994:967.)</i></span>]]></desc><mediaPath src="images/img_p215.jpg" thumbSrc="images/img_p215.jpg"/></mediaPoint>
</mediaMap>
